## 2 ¬∑ Sprint methodology ‚Äî the 7 phases

Each phase's output feeds the next. Run commands in order; don't skip review/QA just because "it worked locally".

| # | Phase     | Primary gstack commands                                                         |
|---|-----------|---------------------------------------------------------------------------------|
| 1 | Think     | `/office-hours`                                                                  |
| 2 | Plan      | `/autoplan` (or manually: `/plan-ceo-review` ‚Üí `/plan-eng-review` ‚Üí `/plan-design-review` ‚Üí `/plan-devex-review`) |
| 3 | Build     | implement, test-first                                                            |
| 4 | Review    | `/review`, `/investigate`, `/codex` (cross-model adversarial)                    |
| 5 | Test      | `/qa` (real browser, atomic commits), `/benchmark`, `/cso` (OWASP + STRIDE)      |
| 6 | Ship      | `/ship` ‚Üí `/land-and-deploy` ‚Üí `/canary`, `/document-release`                    |
| 7 | Reflect   | `/retro`, `/learn`                                                               |

Safety commands available at any time: `/careful`, `/freeze`, `/guard`, `/unfreeze`.

